<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2297: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-17T19:00:00-04:00">May 17, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>49. Your 85, May 16, midnight. We are expressing at Bogotá and at Lima
                            our opinion that the Mello Franco compromise formula, with the proposals
                            he has made to cover the remaining two points, is equitable and offers
                            an honorable and peaceful method of reaching a permanent solution of
                            this controversy. We have expressed hope that the formula may be
                            accepted by both Colombia and Peru.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
